Aim
To capture and analyze TCP, DNS, and HTTP packets using Wireshark filters and examine protocol headers,
source IP addresses, destination IP addresses, and port numbers.
Introduction
Wireshark is a network packet analyzer used to monitor and inspect network traffic in real time. It helps
analyze different protocols such as TCP, DNS, and HTTP by capturing packets transmitted over a network.
Protocol analysis is important in cybersecurity and networking for troubleshooting, monitoring
communication, and understanding packet flow.
Procedure
Step 1: Install Wireshark
1. Download and install Wireshark on Windows or Kali Linux.
2. Launch the Wireshark application.
Step 2: Select Network Interface
1. Choose the active network interface:
• Wi-Fi
• Ethernet
2. Double-click the interface to start packet capture.
Step 3: Generate Network Traffic
Open browser and visit websites such as:
http://example.com
Open terminal and run:
ping google.com
Step 4: Apply Wireshark Filters
TCP Filter
tcp
DNS Filter
dns
HTTP Filter
http
Step 5: Analyze Packets
Observe:
• Source IP address
• Destination IP address
• Port numbers
• TCP communication
• DNS query packets
• HTTP request and response packets
